{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [83, 157], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is Cylinder, Disk, or Sphere, the radius of the light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Radius"], "attrs": {"id": "radius"}, "extent": [57, 66], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [182, 255], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is Cylinder, the length of the light from end to end."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Length"], "attrs": {"id": "length"}, "extent": [157, 165], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [284, 371], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is Geometry, the path to a geometry prim to use as the light shape."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry"], "attrs": {"id": "geometry"}, "extent": [255, 265], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [394, 456], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is Rectangle, the width of the light area."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Width"], "attrs": {"id": "width"}, "extent": [371, 378], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [481, 544], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is Rectangle, the height of the light area."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Height"], "attrs": {"id": "height"}, "extent": [456, 464], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [567, 640], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is Distant, the angular size of the light in degrees."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [640, 785], "text": ["As an example, the Sun is approximately 0.53 degrees as seen from Earth. Higher values broaden the light and therefore soften shadow edges."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Angle"], "attrs": {"id": "angle"}, "extent": [544, 551], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [814, 1150], "text": ["Scales the power output exponentially as a power of 2, similar to an F-stop control. ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, " does not scale intensity, negative numbers scale intensity down by the square, positive numbers scale intensity up. Often you will set the ", {"text": ["Intensity"], "type": "ui"}, " to what looks like the right amount of light, and then use this parameter to \"tweak\" it."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Exposure"], "attrs": {"id": "exposure"}, "extent": [785, 795], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1181, 1235], "text": ["A linear scale on the power output of the light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Intensity"], "attrs": {"id": "intensity"}, "extent": [1150, 1161], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1258, 1311], "text": ["The color of the light, in energy-linear terms."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Color"], "attrs": {"id": "color"}, "extent": [1235, 1242], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1350, 1460], "text": ["Maps a texture to the area geometry of lights. This is currently only supported with rectangular lights."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Texture"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__texturefile_0ta"}, "extent": [1311, 1320], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1519, 1761], "text": ["Use ", {"text": ["Color temperature"], "type": "ui"}, " to control the light color. The color calculated by ", {"text": ["Color temperature"], "type": "ui"}, " is ", {"text": ["multiplied"], "type": "strong"}, " by the RGB color in ", {"text": ["Color"], "type": "ui"}, ", so if you want the \"pure\" temperature color, you should set ", {"text": ["Color"], "type": "ui"}, " to ", {"text": ["1.0, 1.0, 1.0"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable color temperature"], "attrs": {"id": "enableColorTemperature"}, "extent": [1460, 1486], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1807, 2041], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Enable color temperature"], "type": "ui"}, " is on, the temperature (in degrees Kelvin) to simulate. The valid range is from ", {"text": ["1000"], "type": "code"}, " to ", {"text": ["10000"], "type": "code"}, ". Lower values are warmer and higher values are cooler. The default is a common white point, D65."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2041, 2174], "text": ["If necessary, you can compute the same color value using the ", {"text": ["UsdLuxBlackbodyTemperatureAsRgb()"], "type": "code"}, " function from the USD library."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Color temperature"], "attrs": {"id": "colorTemperature"}, "extent": [1761, 1780], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2211, 2435], "text": ["Divides the set power output (intensity scaled by exposure) by the surface area or angular size of the light. This makes it easier to adjust and compare energy output without it being affected by the size of the light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Normalize power"], "attrs": {"id": "normalize"}, "extent": [2174, 2191], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2473, 2579], "text": ["Scales the effect this light has on the diffuse response of shaders. This is a non-physical \"tweak\"."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Diffuse multiplier"], "attrs": {"id": "diffuse"}, "extent": [2435, 2455], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2619, 2726], "text": ["Scales the effect this light has on the specular response of shaders. This is a non-physical \"tweak\"."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Specular multiplier"], "attrs": {"id": "specular"}, "extent": [2579, 2600], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2784, 3039], "text": ["Applies a uniform scaling factor the the guide geometry drawn for the light in the viewport. The default value is an expression that inverts the \"meters per unit\" value of the USD stage to produce a consistent real-world size for the guide geometry."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Scale Guide Geometry"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__houdiniguidescale_s3a"}, "extent": [2726, 2748], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Base properties"], "extent": [16, 57], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "light_base_props"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3113, 3182], "text": ["Add the necessary API to the light to turn it into a spotlight."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Spotlight"], "attrs": {"id": "spotlightenable"}, "extent": [3075, 3087], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3225, 3282], "text": ["The spread angle of the spotlight beam, in degrees."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Angle"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shapingconeangle_51ae"}, "extent": [3182, 3189], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3331, 3412], "text": ["Blurs the edges of the spotlight beam, simulating light leakage and bounce."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Softness"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shapingconesoftness_16ae"}, "extent": [3282, 3292], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3450, 3596], "text": ["Slides in a light blocker from the left, covering part of the spotlight cone. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " reaches all the way across the cone, blocking all light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Left barndoor"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoorleft"}, "extent": [3412, 3427], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3643, 3770], "text": ["Extends the solid light blocker above by an additional soft edge. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " creates a gradient as wide as the spotlight cone."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Left barndoor edge"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoorleftedge"}, "extent": [3596, 3616], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3810, 3957], "text": ["Slides in a light blocker from the right, covering part of the spotlight cone. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " reaches all the way across the cone, blocking all light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Right barndoor"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoorright"}, "extent": [3770, 3786], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4006, 4133], "text": ["Extends the solid light blocker above by an additional soft edge. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " creates a gradient as wide as the spotlight cone."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Right barndoor edge"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoorrightedge"}, "extent": [3957, 3978], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4169, 4314], "text": ["Slides in a light blocker from the top, covering part of the spotlight cone. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " reaches all the way across the cone, blocking all light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Top barndoor"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoortop"}, "extent": [4133, 4147], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4359, 4486], "text": ["Extends the solid light blocker above by an additional soft edge. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " creates a gradient as wide as the spotlight cone."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Top barndoor edge"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoortopedge"}, "extent": [4314, 4333], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4528, 4676], "text": ["Slides in a light blocker from the bottom, covering part of the spotlight cone. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " reaches all the way across the cone, blocking all light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Bottom barndoor"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoorbottom"}, "extent": [4486, 4503], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4727, 4855], "text": ["Extends the solid light blocker above by an additional soft edge. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " creates a gradient as wide as the spotlight cone."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Bottom barndoor edge"], "attrs": {"id": "barndoorbottomedge"}, "extent": [4676, 4698], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "sep", "extent": [4855, 4861], "level": 5}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4902, 4972], "text": ["Add the necessary API to the light to be able to focus the beam."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Focus (checkbox)"], "attrs": {"id": "focusenable"}, "extent": [4861, 4880], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5010, 5188], "text": ["A control to shape the spread of light. Higher focus values pull light towards the center and narrow the spread. (This is implemented as an off-axis cosine power exponent.)"]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Focus"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shapingfocus_nva"}, "extent": [4972, 4979], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5235, 5323], "text": ["Off-axis color tint, tints the light in the falloff region. The default is black."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Focus tint"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shapingfocusTint_51a"}, "extent": [5188, 5200], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "sep", "extent": [5323, 5329], "level": 5}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5355, 5456], "text": ["Add the necessary API to the light to use an IES file describing angular distribution of light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["IES"], "attrs": {"id": "iesenable"}, "extent": [5329, 5335], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5496, 5604], "text": ["An IES (Illumination Engineering Society) format file to use to control angular distribution of light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["File"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shapingiesfile_wyad"}, "extent": [5456, 5462], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5657, 5711], "text": ["A global scale on angles found in the IES file."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Angle scale"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shapingiesangleScale_o8ad"}, "extent": [5604, 5617], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Shaping"], "extent": [3039, 3075], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "light_shaping_props"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5779, 5872], "text": ["When this is on, objects hit by this light will cast shadows (subject to shadow masks)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shadowenable_mva"}, "extent": [5739, 5748], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5909, 6025], "text": ["Tints the color of shadows cast by this light. Changing this from black (", {"text": ["0, 0, 0"], "type": "code"}, ") is a non-physical \"tweak\"."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Color"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shadowcolor_zta"}, "extent": [5872, 5879], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6066, 6121], "text": ["The near distance at which shadow falloff begins."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6121, 6171], "text": ["The default value (-1) indicates no falloff."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Falloff"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shadowfalloff_8wa"}, "extent": [6025, 6034], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6223, 6369], "text": ["A gamma (i.e., exponential) control over shadow strength with linear distance within the falloff zone (between ", {"text": ["Falloff"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Distance"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Falloff Gamma"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shadowfalloffGamma_e5a"}, "extent": [6171, 6186], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6412, 6630], "text": ["The maximum distance to check for objects shadowing this light. The default is ", {"text": ["-1"], "type": "code"}, ", meaning no limit. Setting this may speed up rendering if you know all objects you want shadowed are within a certain distance."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance"], "attrs": {"id": "xn__shadowdistance_vya"}, "extent": [6369, 6379], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Shadow"], "extent": [5711, 5739], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "shadow_props"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [18293, 18350], "text": ["Outside this radius, the light will have no effect."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Active Radius"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"kagroup": "Light", "hprop": "karma:light:activeradius"}, "extent": [18218, 18235], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "karma:light:activeradius"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [19053, 19174], "text": ["Controls whether multiple importance sampling will sample from the BSDF,\n    the light, or both the BSDF and light."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["MIS Bias"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "karma:light:misbias", "kagroup": "Shading"}, "extent": [18986, 18998], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "karma:light:misbias"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [19258, 19464], "text": ["This is the per-light sampling quality.  Increasing the quality will add\n    additional samples for this light source, improving the sampling quality\n    of this light relative to other light sources."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Sampling Quality"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "karma:light:samplingquality", "kagroup": "Sampling"}, "extent": [19174, 19194], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "karma:light:samplingquality"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [22109, 22427], "text": ["When using the light tree for rendering, Karma will try to put any light\n    source that\u2019s compatible into the tree.  This option can force a light to\n    be excluded from the tree and subject to uniform sampling, which can \n    sometimes yield an improved sampling quality the light at the expense\n    of speed."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Force Uniform Sampling"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "karma:light:force_uniform_sampling", "kagroup": "Sampling"}, "extent": [22012, 22038], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "karma:light:force_uniform_sampling"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [22654, 22734], "text": ["The category identifier used to select this light source for illumination."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Category"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "karma:light:category", "kagroup": "Shading"}, "extent": [22586, 22598], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "karma:light:category"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [22818, 23075], "text": ["If an environment map is larger than this resolution, it will be scaled\n    down when performing texture analysis.  If the map has some very small,\n    very bright values, this filtering may affect how sampling of the\n    environment map is performed."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Maximum HDRI Size"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "karma:light:hdri_max_isize", "kagroup": "Sampling"}, "extent": [22734, 22755], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "karma:light:hdri_max_isize"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Karma"], "extent": [6630, 6662], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "karma_light_props"}], "included": ["/props/karma"], "type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "include"}}